Durban - Several reports, including a psychological evaluation of a 10-year-old girl, who was repeatedly raped by her stepfather over a period spanning half her life, are still outstanding in the case against him. 
The 43-year-old man made a brief appearance at the Verulam Magistrates Court on Thursday, with the court’s video remand system from Westville Prison.
The man - who cannot be named to protect the girl’s identity - is accused of raping and otherwise sexually assaulting her, sexual grooming and exposing his stepdaughter to pornography.
He was arrested in June and the girl was rescued and taken to a place of safety. 
