The girl’s maternal relatives, who live in KwaDukuza, have since come forward and said that the stepfather had refused to let the girl live with them. AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads
The man was denied bail in July, as Magistrate Irfaan Khalil found that it was not in the interests of justice to release the man on bail.
He said he had considered a petition signed by about 100 community members and that, if given bail, the community would likely be outraged.
The case was adjourned to October and the man was remanded in custody.

